The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining strongly connected components and single source reachability in graphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and algorithms. The paper also mentions previous work on these problems, which have been studied extensively in the computer science community. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
